      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Website Builders</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-6">How To Build A Mobile App For Your Front-Commerce Website</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8">Want to build a mobile app for your Front-Commerce website, without hundreds of thousands of dollars of investment? MobiLoud makes it easy. See how it works inside.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-slate">
      <p id>Want to convert your <a href="https://www.front-commerce.com/" id>Front-Commerce</a> website into a mobile app? MobiLoud is here to help.</p><p id>With <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a>, converting your Front-Commerce website into a mobile app for iOS and Android is easier than ever. There’s no need to rebuild anything or maintain a separate platform, it's no-code, and you'll be able to fully replicate your website experience in the app.</p><p id>In this article you will learn more about the benefits of mobile apps to your business, other options to build your apps, and why MobiLoud is the best option among them.</p><blockquote id>MobiLoud is the proven and risk-free option for eCommerce sites wanting to launch their own mobile app, without a massive investment. <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Book a demo now</a> to learn how we help you launch mobile apps that deliver a positive ROI.</blockquote><h2 id>Why You Should Build a Mobile App For Your Front-Commerce Website</h2><p id>Remember when having a nice shopfront and ads in the local newspaper was enough to keep a business afloat? </p><p id>Times have changed, and with technology getting better every day, this has also led to a change in consumer habits.&nbsp;</p><p id><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/249855/mobile-retail-commerce-revenue-in-the-united-states/" id>Data shows</a> that in the United States alone, mobile commerce sales exceeded 491 billion USD in 2023 and it is now forecasted to grow almost double by 2027.&nbsp;</p><p id>This follows the overall trend of mobile internet usage, which currently accounts for approximately <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/what-percentage-of-internet-traffic-is-mobile" id>57% of all internet traffic</a>.</p><p id>What's more, <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/fact-sheet/mobile/" id>15% of Americans today are smartphone-only</a>, meaning they only access the internet via their mobile devices. This is the future of eCommerce - customers who aren’t just mobile-first, but <em id>mobile-only</em>.</p><p id>Optimizing your site for mobile is a nice start, but it's no longer enough. Apps provide a superior user experience on mobile, which leads to increases in a number of key metrics, such as:</p><ul id><li id>Increased conversion rates</li><li id>Higher average order value</li><li id>More products viewed per session</li></ul><p id>More data shows that eCommerce mobile app users are twice as likely to return to the store within 30 days, compared to those on mobile browsers.</p><p id>Apps are a great tool to nurture loyal, repeat customers, and also give you full use of mobile push notifications, which have, on average, 20% open rates and 28% click-through rates.</p><p id>Do you "need" to turn your online store into a mobile app? Perhaps not. But a mobile app can have these massive benefits for your business:</p><h3 id>A better mobile shopping experience</h3><p id>Your customers will have a better time shopping on mobile than on your mobile website. Your store will be easier to navigate, with fewer of the annoyances and distractions you get when shopping on a mobile website. A mobile app allows them to shop anywhere and anytime.</p><h3 id>Increased loyalty and retention</h3><p id>The better user experience directly correlates to increased loyalty and retention. If people love shopping with you, they'll come back and do it again.</p><p id>Apps are tailor-made for fostering loyalty and increasing retention rates. They make it easy for people to get in, with just one tap from their home screen. And that home screen icon is a constant reminder of your brand, a permanent fixture in your customers' headspace.</p><p id>This is all going to translate to a higher lifetime value from every one of your app users.</p><h3 id>An owned sales channel</h3><p id>Worried about a dip in Google SEO rankings, or the constant cost of driving traffic from paid ads?</p><p id>An app gives you an owned channel, not susceptible to the platform risk of Google, Facebook, or online marketplaces.</p><p id>You can reach out directly to your customers through push notifications, and re-engage your customers, even if your reach on external platforms is diminished for whatever reason.</p><h3 id>App store presence</h3><p id>Finally, getting into the app stores is a powerful thing.</p><p id>They can provide a new acquisition channel. They also provide a ton of social proof. When someone sees you have a mobile app in the iOS App Store or Google Play Store, your brand instantly looks more legitimate and trustworthy.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-center" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="center" data-rt-max-width><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/67075e2f0cef346a43f19076_67075e2a19ccf129272c8b75_670595a58cd21d6631596ce2_jv-app-stores.avif" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div></figure><h2 id>How to&nbsp;Build a Mobile App For Your Front-Commerce Website</h2><p id>If speed, cost-efficiency, and maintaining your existing site’s functionality are top priorities, <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a> offers a solid solution to build a mobile app out of your website.</p><p id>Our platform allows you to convert your existing website into a fully functional mobile app for both iOS and Android, without the need to rebuild everything from scratch. </p><p id>Our approach leverages the responsive design of your website, packaging it into a native app that can be distributed via the app stores. It supports native features like push notifications, offline functionality, and in-app purchases, providing a smooth mobile experience for your users. </p><p id>Since you’re not starting from scratch, this approach saves time and money, making it a smart choice for businesses that want to go mobile without the high costs of custom development.</p><p id>If you’re a big brand with a ton of resources at your disposal, you might be able to afford rebuilding from scratch using these options:<br><br><strong id>Custom Native Development</strong>: This is the most customizable option, where you build separate apps for iOS and Android (which doubles the development time and cost). While this offers full control, it’s also expensive and time-consuming, requiring a dedicated team of developers to create and maintain the app.&nbsp;</p><p id><strong id>Cross-Platform Development</strong>: Frameworks like React Native or Flutter allow you to build a single codebase that works across both platforms. This is faster and more affordable than custom development but still requires a substantial level of coding expertise and cost as you will still need to hire a team of developers to create and maintain the app for you.</p><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/how-much-does-it-cost-to-create-an-app" id>Mobile app development costs a lot</a>, and adds a lot of ongoing work, which comes with significant overhead expenses. Keep in mind that the right choice depends on your business's specific needs, budget, and timeline.</p><h2 id>Convert Your Front-Commerce Website to a Mobile App With MobiLoud Today</h2><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a> lets you skip the pain and high cost of mobile app development. Our platform can turn any website into native mobile apps. It’s a done-for-you service that has the best elements of a no code app builder and custom app development.</p><p id>With MobiLoud, you can launch apps with zero coding and zero technical ability. There’s no need to hire and manage developers, and you won’t even have to spend money close to the level of investment needed to build fully custom apps from the ground up.</p><p id>Our solution doesn’t limit you to blocks and templates. It fully converts your existing website into apps, which are fully synced with your site to make the apps simple to update and maintain.</p><p id>You can ship a <em id>full-featured mobile app</em> that carries over all the features of your website, and feels like a fully custom native app to the end user, for minimal cost, done in less than a month.</p><h3 id>How It Works</h3><p id>With MobiLoud, your app will be a full, live reflection of your website. We strip away the browser tabs, and add a few small native mobile touches, such as navigation UI, a tab menu and splash screens. We then put together native code to allow your app to run in Android and iOS operating systems, and let you send native mobile push notifications.</p><p id>Our approach has a number of advantages:</p><ul id><li id>It lets you quickly and easily go to market with an app, as you don’t need to rebuild or drastically redesign anything.</li><li id>Maintenance is much easier, since you’re using the same codebase for your site and your apps. When you update your site, your apps update automatically.</li><li id>All the features on your website, such as plugins, themes, widgets, integrations, payment gateways and any custom features will work in the app in the same way.</li><li id>There’s no coding, no technical knowledge needed from you or your team.</li><li id>You can be totally hands-off and launch with zero addition to your existing workflow.</li></ul><p id>Our full-service approach covers every part of the process. This includes:</p><ul id><li id>Development work to convert your site into apps and deploy it for Android and iOS.</li><li id>Configuring your app to ensure it feels fully native to the end user.</li><li id>Custom UI/UX tweaks to your mobile website to maximize your mobile user experience in both app and website.</li><li id>Submitting your app to the Apple and Google Play app stores, and handling all back-and-forths to ensure your app and listing meet their standards.</li><li id>Handling technical updates and maintenance for your app after launching.</li></ul><p id>The process starts with a <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>kick-off call</a> with one of our project managers. We’ll discuss your needs and what you want to get out of the project, and make sure MobiLoud is right for you.</p><p id>From there, we take over to build and launch your apps, keeping you updated every step of the way.</p><p id>From start to finish, you can be live and in the app stores in less than a month, for a low-four figure investment, plus a guarantee that your app will be accepted into the app stores, so it’s completely risk-free.</p><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/pricing" id>Learn more about our pricing here</a>.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f376e06e08bf7d6a29_20250702T0913-cc627ec2-99cc-46f6-81fd-923171fb4f1b.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div><figcaption id>A few <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/examples" id>examples</a> of the amazing apps we've built for high-revenue eCommerce brands</figcaption></figure><p id>Our done-for-you service allows you to launch your own shopping apps, and take your place in the app stores alongside the world's biggest brands.</p><p id>Get in touch with us now to learn more about how we can help you launch an app for your Front-Commerce store. Just <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>book a free consultation</a> and one of our app experts will walk you through the whole process.</p>
    </div>
